IN THE COURT OF THE {{COURT_NAME}}
AT {{COURT_PLACE}}

O.S. No. {{SUIT_NUMBER}} / {{SUIT_YEAR}}

Territorial jurisdiction: The Defendant resides and carries on business at {{DEFENDANT_ADDRESS}}, which lies within the local limits of this Court's territorial jurisdiction. The Plaintiff advanced Rs. 5,00,000 to the Defendant on 10.03.2024 as a hand loan and handed over the amount at {{LOAN_DISBURSEMENT_LOCATION}}; The loan was evidenced by a promissory note executed on 10.03.2024 at {{AGREEMENT_PLACE}}. The loan was repayable on demand or within six months as per the promissory note. The cause of action first arose on 15.09.2024 when the Plaintiff sent a demand for repayment; A legal notice demanding repayment was issued on 20.09.2024; This suit is filed in the Civil Judge Senior Division at {{COURT_PLACE}}, {{STATE}}. The above facts establish a concrete territorial link: the Defendant's residence and business fall within the jurisdiction of this Court, and the loan transaction and agreement location are within the same territorial limits.

Pecuniary jurisdiction: The Plaintiff seeks Rs. 5,00,000. This amount falls within this Court's monetary limits for suits to be tried by a Civil Judge Senior Division in {{STATE}}.

